TITLE: Modifying TTL and Removing Set-Cookie Headers in Varnish Backend Response
DESCRIPTION: This VCL snippet overrides the TTL for image files and removes Set-Cookie headers to prevent the creation of hit-for-miss objects. It's implemented in the vcl_backend_response subroutine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/vcl-example-manipulating-responses.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: vcl
CODE:
```
sub vcl_backend_response {
   if (bereq.url ~ "\.(png|gif|jpg)$") {
     unset beresp.http.set-cookie;
     set beresp.ttl = 1h;
  }
}
```

