TITLE: Creating and Using an Access Control List (ACL) in VCL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates defining an ACL named 'localnetwork' with IP addresses and hostnames, then using it to match against the client's IP address. The example includes a positive match, a network match, and a negative match.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/reference/vcl.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: vcl
CODE:
```
acl localnetwork {
    "localhost";    # myself
    "192.0.2.0"/24; # and everyone on the local network
    ! "192.0.2.23"; # except for the dial-in router
}
```

