TITLE: Implementing Health Checks for Backends in Varnish VCL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to implement health checks for backend servers in VCL. It defines backends with probe configurations and sets up a round-robin director with these backends.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/vcl-backends.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: VCL
CODE:
```
backend server1 {
    .host = "server1.example.com";
    .probe = {
        .url = "/";
        .timeout = 1s;
        .interval = 5s;
        .window = 5;
        .threshold = 3;
    }
}

backend server2 {
    .host = "server2.example.com";
    .probe = {
        .url = "/";
        .timeout = 1s;
        .interval = 5s;
        .window = 5;
        .threshold = 3;
    }
}

import directors;

sub vcl_init {
    new vdir = directors.round_robin();
    vdir.add_backend(server1);
    vdir.add_backend(server2);
}
```

