TITLE: Layering Directors in Varnish VCL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to layer directors in VCL. It creates two round-robin directors and combines them into a fallback director, allowing for more complex load balancing strategies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/vcl-backends.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: VCL
CODE:
```
import directors;

sub vcl_init {
    new dc1 = directors.round_robin();
    dc1.add_backend(server1A);
    dc1.add_backend(server1B);

    new dc2 = directors.round_robin();
    dc2.add_backend(server2A);
    dc2.add_backend(server2B);

    new dcprio = directors.fallback();
    dcprio.add_backend(dc1);
    dcprio.add_backend(dc2);
}
```

