TITLE: Default VCL Hash Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Default hashing configuration in Varnish that uses URL and Host header (or server IP) to generate cache keys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/vcl-hashing.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: vcl
CODE:
```
sub vcl_hash {
    hash_data(req.url);
    if (req.http.host) {
        hash_data(req.http.host);
    } else {
        hash_data(server.ip);
    }
    return (lookup);
}
```

