TITLE: Setting Hit-for-Pass in VCL Backend Response
DESCRIPTION: This VCL snippet shows how to set an object to hit-for-pass state for a specific duration when the TTL is 0 and the response headers allow for validation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/increasing-your-hitrate.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: vcl
CODE:
```
sub vcl_backend_response {
  # Set hit-for-pass for two minutes if TTL is 0 and response headers
  # allow for validation.
  if (beresp.ttl <= 0s && (beresp.http.ETag || beresp.http.Last-Modified)) {
    return(pass(120s));
  }
}
```

