TITLE: Defining vcl_recv Subroutine in VCL
DESCRIPTION: The vcl_recv subroutine is called at the beginning of a request. It decides whether to serve the request, modify it, or how to process it further. It can return various keywords to control request flow.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/reference/vcl_step.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: VCL
CODE:
```
vcl_recv {
  # Decision logic goes here
  return (hash); # Example return value
}
```

