TITLE: Setting Up Directors for Load Balancing in Varnish VCL
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set up a round-robin director for load balancing in VCL. It defines multiple backends, creates a director, and assigns backends to it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/vcl-backends.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: VCL
CODE:
```
import directors;

backend server1 {
    .host = "192.168.0.10";
}
backend server2 {
    .host = "192.168.0.11";
}

sub vcl_init {
    new bar = directors.round_robin();
    bar.add_backend(server1);
    bar.add_backend(server2);
}

sub vcl_recv {
    # send all traffic to the bar director:
    set req.backend_hint = bar.backend();
}
```

