TITLE: Preventing 304 Responses on Hit-for-Miss in VCL
DESCRIPTION: This VCL snippet demonstrates how to prevent Varnish from sending 304 responses to the client on hit-for-miss by removing If-None-Match and If-Modified-Since headers in vcl_miss.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/increasing-your-hitrate.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: vcl
CODE:
```
sub vcl_miss {
  # To prevent 304 client responses on hit-for-miss.
  unset req.http.If-None-Match;
  unset req.http.If-Modified-Since;
}
```

