TITLE: Implementing HTTP PURGE in VCL
DESCRIPTION: VCL configuration to enable HTTP PURGE functionality with ACL restrictions. Allows purging cached objects from localhost and specific IP range.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/users-guide/purging.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: vcl
CODE:
```
acl purge {
  "localhost";
  "192.168.55.0"/24;
}

sub vcl_recv {
      # allow PURGE from localhost and 192.168.55...

  if (req.method == "PURGE") {
      if (!client.ip ~ purge) {
          return(synth(405,"Not allowed."));
      }
      return (purge);
  }
}
```

