TITLE: VCL Language BNF Grammar Definition
DESCRIPTION: Backus-Naur Form (BNF) grammar definition for the Varnish Configuration Language (VCL). This defines the basic syntax structure including program composition, functions, statements, and control flow constructs that would form the foundation of VCL.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/phk/firstdesign.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bnf
CODE:
```
program:	function
		| program function

function:	"sub" function_name compound_statement

compound_statement:	"{" statements "}"

statements:	/* empty */
		| statement
		| statements statement


statement:	if_statement
		| call_statement
		| "finish"
		| assignment_statement
		| action_statement

if_statement:	"if" condition compound_statement elif_parts else_part
```

