TITLE: Transaction Hierarchy Example in VSL Query
DESCRIPTION: Example showing the hierarchical structure of transactions in request grouping mode, demonstrating different levels of client requests, backend requests, and ESI subrequests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/reference/vsl-query.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: txt
CODE:
```
Lvl 1: Client request (cache miss)
  Lvl 2: Backend request
  Lvl 2: ESI subrequest (cache miss)
    Lvl 3: Backend request
    Lvl 3: Backend request (VCL restart)
    Lvl 3: ESI subrequest (cache miss)
