TITLE: Implementing Timed Lock Acquisition in C
DESCRIPTION: A code example demonstrating how programmers typically implement timed lock acquisition in threaded code, showing the problem with wall-clock based timeouts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/varnishcache/varnish-cache/blob/master/doc/sphinx/phk/thetoolsweworkwith.rst#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
int
get_lock_timed(lock, timeout)
{
	while (timeout > 0) {
		t0 = time();
		i = get_lock_before(lock, t + timeout));
		if (i == WASLOCKED)
			return (i);
		t1 = time();
		timeout -= (t1 - t0);
	}
	return (TIMEDOUT);
}
```

